    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest, no-nonsense car that\u2019s best suited for someone after cheap wheels, a handy project, or a parts donor. It\u2019s not a showpiece, but it\u2019s got plenty of potential for the right buyer and could be a great value if you know your way around cars. Priced fairly for what it is and sold with a straightforward, friendly approach.",
      "price": 6800.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 34
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Driver-grade project with solid enthusiast upside. The drivetrain fires up and the car has the kind of analog, mechanical character that\u2019s getting harder to find\u2014responsive steering feel, honest chassis feedback, and a platform that rewards someone willing to sort the details. It shows wear inside and out and should be considered a poor-condition vehicle, but it appears largely complete and is a strong candidate for a budget build, parts donor, or weekend restoration. If you want an affordable entry point into an engaging platform with real potential, this is worth a look.",
      "price": 6900.0,
